com.exacttarget.etpushsdk

Class ETAnalytics

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.exacttarget.etpushsdk.ETAnalytics

  • public class ETAnalytics
extends Object
    Analytics for Journey Builder for Apps (JB4A) SDK.

    ETAnalytics will send its data 15 seconds after the last time activityPaused() method is called on ETPush. If you're switching between activities in a foreground app, this will *not* trigger a data upload. Only when the app truly goes into the background and no call to activityResumed() has happened for over 15 seconds will ETAnalytics upload tracking data.

    The following is required only if you are targetting earlier than Android API 14. For apps targetting Android 14 or later, the SDK will implement these calls using registerActivityLifecycleCallbacks().

     
 public class MyActivity extends Activity {
  ...
  @Override
  protected void onResume() {
    super.onResume();
    try {
      ETPush.activityResumed(this);
    }
    catch(ETException e) {
      LogIt.e(TAG, e.getMessage(), e);
    }
  }

  @Override
  protected void onPause() {
    super.onPause();
    try {
      ETPush.activityPaused(this);
    }
    catch(ETException e) {
      LogIt.e(TAG, e.getMessage(), e);
    }
  }
  ...
 }
